			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				ok n00bs, a couple of things. 1) this is an old post from 1999! 2) the runes can be obtained from doing the Staff of the Wheel quest. They are no drop runes. 3) I've bought the runes at vendors in FV and Thurg. These are NOT no drop runes. If you make the spell from no drop runes the spell is no drop, whereas if you make it from runes that drop off mobs the spell can be sold or bought. You need a very high research skill. I'd say atleast 150 to even think about attempting. Wear wis gear to increase the chance of result. I'd say get your wis up above 150 (the higher the better). I made the spell with a research skill of 165 and wis of 155 on the second attempt. Yes I had two sets of runes I bought. I did do the SotW quest but still have the staff =P (very nice staff). 5) this is still an awesome spell even tho there are better ones. 6) this spell is a measure of a Wizard much like the SotW quest is. Kinda like a status symbol. you dont get this spell you will be looked down apon by others as not being a &quot;real&quot; wizard. GET IT and do the SotW quest. You will only become a better wizard.
				</font>
